div.span: Turbulent Advocates are Introverted, Intuitive, Feeling, Judging and Turbulent. Advocates are quiet visionaries, often serving as inspiring and tireless idealists. These rare types are open-minded and imaginative, applying care and creativity.
Diplomats focus on empathy and cooperation, shining in diplomacy and counselling. They’re imaginative, warm, empathic, and influential people, often playing the role of harmonizers.
Constant Improvers are quiet, individualistic, perfectionistic, and success-driven people, often spending a lot of time and effort ensuring the result of their work is the best it can be.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely very imaginative and open-minded, focusing on hidden meanings and distant possibilities.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely decisive, thorough, and highly organized. Values clarity and prefers planning to spontaneity.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
